

update /etc/apt/sources.list by removing everything and adding those lines:

#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#
#                            OFFICIAL UBUNTU REPOS                             #
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------#


###### Ubuntu Main Repos
deb http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic main restricted universe multiverse 
deb-src http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic main restricted universe multiverse 

###### Ubuntu Update Repos
deb http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-security main restricted universe multiverse 
deb http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-updates main restricted universe multiverse 
deb http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-proposed main restricted universe multiverse 
deb http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-backports main restricted universe multiverse 
deb-src http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-security main restricted universe multiverse 
deb-src http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-updates main restricted universe multiverse 
deb-src http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-proposed main restricted universe multiverse 
deb-src http://sa.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/ bionic-backports main restricted universe multiverse 

-------------------

sudo apt update
sudo apt install php-xdebug 

-------------------
in /etc/php/7.2/mods-available/xdebug.ini
add those lines 

xdebug.remote_host=10.0.2.2
xdebug.remote_enable=1
xdebug.remote_connect_back=1
xdebug.remote_port=9000
xdebug.idekey="PHPSTORM"

--------------------
exit 
vagrant reload 

in phpstorm do the following after finishing up with the vagrant box:
preferences -> languages & frameworks -> php -> cli interpeters ... -> + -> vagrant -> add 
Run Menu -> Edit Configuration -> + -> PHP Web Page -> Server ... -> Set path mapping -> Apply -> Ok -> Start URL = \

And VOILLA !!!!! ENJOY :)
